$ Row based / column based Databases

~Column format~ is efficient for analytics (→ development/Data/OLAP) because it can limit read access to data to relevant data only.

~Row format~ is efficient for → development/Data/OLTP because it's easy to insert, update or delete records.

Generally, column stores are suitable for read-intensive and large data amounts.

Some claim that column-stores offer better compression (because similar data formats and values go together).

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/In-Memory-Area[Oracle's columnar-format].
